{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Control Systems Analysis\n\nThis notebook demonstrates state-space control systems analysis using Maxima's symbolic capabilities combined with numerical computation from `numerics`. We analyse linear time-invariant systems in state-space form:\n\n$$\\frac{d\\mathbf{x}}{dt} = A\\mathbf{x} + B\\mathbf{u}, \\quad \\mathbf{y} = C\\mathbf{x}$$\n\nStarting from circuit equations, we derive the state-space model symbolically, then use numerical tools for eigenvalue analysis, step response simulation, and frequency response (Bode) plots.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 13,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## RLC Circuit as State-Space System [S+N]\n\nConsider a series RLC circuit driven by an input voltage $V_{\\text{in}}$. The two energy-storage elements (inductor $L$ and capacitor $C$) give rise to two state variables: the inductor current $i_L$ and the capacitor voltage $v_C$.\n\nFrom Kirchhoff's voltage law:\n- $L \\frac{di_L}{dt} = -R\\,i_L - v_C + V_{\\text{in}}$\n- $C \\frac{dv_C}{dt} = i_L$\n\nWriting in state-space form with $\\mathbf{x} = [i_L,\\; v_C]^T$ and $u = V_{\\text{in}}$:",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* RLC series circuit: L*di/dt = -R*i - v_C + V_in */\n/*                     C*dv_C/dt = i                 */\n/* State: x = [i_L, v_C], Input: u = V_in            */\n/* dx/dt = A*x + B*u                                 */\nA_sym : matrix([-R/L, -1/L], [1/C_cap, 0]);\nB_sym : matrix([1/L], [0]);\nC_out : matrix([0, 1]);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "matrix([-(R/L),-(1/L)],[1/C_cap,0])\nmatrix([1/L],[0])"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 0&1\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 14,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Substitute numeric values: R=1 Ohm, L=0.5 H, C=1 F */\nparams : [R=1, L=1/2, C_cap=1]$\nA_num : subst(params, A_sym)$\nprint(\"A (numeric) =\", A_num)$\n\nA : ndarray(float(A_num))$\nB : ndarray(float(subst(params, B_sym)))$\nprint(\"A ndarray:\", A)$\nprint(\"B ndarray:\", B)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "A (numeric) = matrix([-2,-2],[1,0])\nA ndarray: ndarray(\\#\\<ndarray\\ 1\\ DOUBLE\\-FLOAT\\ \\(2\\ 2\\)\\>)\nB ndarray: ndarray(\\#\\<ndarray\\ 2\\ DOUBLE\\-FLOAT\\ \\(2\\ 1\\)\\>)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Eigenvalue Analysis — Stability [S+N]\n\nThe stability of a linear system is determined by its eigenvalues. If all eigenvalues have strictly negative real parts, the system is asymptotically stable. The eigenvalues also reveal the natural frequency $\\omega_n$ and damping ratio $\\zeta$.\n\nFor a 2nd-order system with characteristic polynomial $s^2 + 2\\zeta\\omega_n s + \\omega_n^2 = 0$:\n- $\\omega_n = \\sqrt{\\det(A)}$\n- $2\\zeta\\omega_n = -\\text{tr}(A)$",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic eigenvalue analysis */\nchar_poly : charpoly(A_sym, s);\nprint(\"Characteristic polynomial:\", char_poly)$\n\n/* Solve for eigenvalues symbolically */\nevals_sym : solve(char_poly, s);\nprint(\"Symbolic eigenvalues:\", evals_sym)$\n\n/* Numeric eigenvalue computation via np_eig */\n[evals_nd, evecs_nd] : np_eig(A)$\nprint(\"Numeric eigenvalues:\", evals_nd)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "1/(C_cap*L)-(-s-R/L)*s\nCharacteristic polynomial: 1/(C_cap*L)-(-s-R/L)*s\n[s = -((sqrt(C_cap^2*R^2-4*C_cap*L)+C_cap*R)/(2*C_cap*L)),\n s = (sqrt(C_cap^2*R^2-4*C_cap*L)-C_cap*R)/(2*C_cap*L)]\nSymbolic eigenvalues:\n                     [s = -((sqrt(C_cap^2*R^2-4*C_cap*L)+C_cap*R)\n                        /(2*C_cap*L)),\n                      s = (sqrt(C_cap^2*R^2-4*C_cap*L)-C_cap*R)/(2*C_cap*L)]\nNumeric eigenvalues: ndarray(\\#\\<ndarray\\ 3\\ COMPLEX\\-DOUBLE\\-FLOAT\\ \\(2\\)\\>)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Natural frequency and damping ratio */\nomega_n : sqrt(subst(params, 1/(L*C_cap)));\nzeta : subst(params, R / (2*sqrt(L/C_cap)));\n\nprint(\"Natural frequency omega_n =\", omega_n)$\nprint(\"Damping ratio zeta =\", zeta)$\n\nif zeta < 1 then print(\"System is underdamped\")\nelseif zeta = 1 then print(\"System is critically damped\")\nelse print(\"System is overdamped\")$\n\n/* Check stability: all eigenvalues have negative real parts */\nprint(\"All eigenvalues have Re < 0 (stable):\",\n  is(subst(params, realpart(rhs(evals_sym[1]))) < 0)\n  and is(subst(params, realpart(rhs(evals_sym[2]))) < 0))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 17,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "sqrt(2)\n1/sqrt(2)\nNatural frequency omega_n = sqrt(2)\nDamping ratio zeta = 1/sqrt(2)\nSystem is underdamped\nAll eigenvalues have Re < 0 (stable): true"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Step Response via Matrix Exponential\n\nFor a step input $u = 1$ applied at $t = 0$ with zero initial conditions, the state evolves as:\n\n$$\\mathbf{x}(t + \\Delta t) = e^{A \\Delta t}\\,\\mathbf{x}(t) + \\Delta t \\cdot B\\,u$$\n\nThis simple Euler-like time-stepping with the matrix exponential $e^{A\\Delta t}$ (computed once via `np_expm`) gives the step response trajectories for both state variables.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Time-stepping for step response */\ndt : 0.01$\nnt : 500$\nt_vals : makelist(i * dt, i, 0, nt - 1)$\n\n/* Precompute matrix exponential for one time step */\neAdt : np_expm(np_scale(dt, A))$\n\n/* Step input as a 1x1 matrix */\nu_step : ndarray(matrix([1.0]))$\nBu : np_scale(dt, np_matmul(B, u_step))$\n\n/* Simulate */\nx : np_zeros([2, 1])$  /* initial state: [i_L=0, v_C=0] */\ni_out : []$\nv_out : []$\nfor k : 1 thru nt do (\n  i_out : endcons(np_ref(x, 0, 0), i_out),\n  v_out : endcons(np_ref(x, 1, 0), v_out),\n  x : np_add(np_matmul(eAdt, x), Bu)\n)$\n\nprint(\"Simulation complete:\", nt, \"time steps\")$\nprint(\"Final i_L =\", last(i_out), \", Final v_C =\", last(v_out))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 18,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Simulation complete: 500 time steps\nFinal i_L = -0.0031410220404779685 , Final v_C = 1.0047288668145948"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot step response: current i_L(t) and voltage v_C(t) */\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"i_L(t) — current\",\n  lines(t_vals, i_out),\n  color=\"red\", line_width=2, name=\"v_C(t) — voltage\",\n  lines(t_vals, v_out),\n  title=\"Step Response of RLC Circuit\",\n  xlabel=\"Time (s)\", ylabel=\"Amplitude\",\n  showlegend=true, grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": [
        {
